279
00:23:10,021 --> 00:23:11,341
Found out last year.

280
00:23:13,454 --> 00:23:14,914
And now she has cancer.

281
00:23:27,338 --> 00:23:28,765
I'm sorry to hear that.

282
00:23:35,649 --> 00:23:36,836
When I warned you,

283
00:23:37,569 --> 00:23:39,219
I did it as an older sister.

284
00:23:42,216 --> 00:23:45,365
You still have a long life ahead of you.

285
00:23:46,455 --> 00:23:47,889
It's not too late to quit.

286
00:24:01,319 --> 00:24:03,076
So...

287
00:24:03,625 --> 00:24:06,756
You became a teacher here because of your mom?

288
00:24:09,886 --> 00:24:11,526
Is the money that good?

289
00:24:13,683 --> 00:24:15,009
The benefits are good.

290
00:24:16,560 --> 00:24:19,137
And I have time after work to see her.

291
00:24:20,981 --> 00:24:22,007
Also,

292
00:24:24,650 --> 00:24:26,524
I get a bonus if my students compete.

293
00:24:27,841 --> 00:24:30,236
So asking me to compete...

294
00:24:30,237 --> 00:24:33,023
It's because I'm part of getting your bonus?

295
00:24:34,194 --> 00:24:36,796
I'd be lying if I said it wasn't.

296
00:24:43,009 --> 00:24:44,929
But I truly believe in you, Belle.

297
00:24:50,743 --> 00:24:52,076
I know.

298
00:24:52,615 --> 00:24:54,142
You've said it many times.

299
00:24:54,981 --> 00:24:56,928
Even in front of Teacher Thip.

300
00:24:57,630 --> 00:24:59,630
My aunt has never even said that.

301
00:25:09,266 --> 00:25:11,026
Just do your best.

302
00:25:12,168 --> 00:25:14,574
And in the meantime, behave yourself.

303
00:25:15,229 --> 00:25:16,916
Or you might not get to compete.

304
00:25:18,337 --> 00:25:20,888
You finally got moved to a normal class.

305
00:25:21,603 --> 00:25:23,522
Instead of detention.

306
00:25:23,857 --> 00:25:25,737
Try to stay there.

307
00:25:29,974 --> 00:25:32,089
Are you worried as a teacher,

308
00:25:33,014 --> 00:25:34,641
or as a sister?

309
00:25:39,379 --> 00:25:40,757
Let's do this.

310
00:25:44,183 --> 00:25:45,565
On this rooftop...

311
00:25:47,139 --> 00:25:48,404
there's no Teacher Nalin.

312
00:25:50,552 --> 00:25:52,732
And no student named Belle.

313
00:25:54,524 --> 00:25:57,788
Just an older and younger sister.

314
00:26:00,359 --> 00:26:01,700
If...

315
00:26:02,393 --> 00:26:04,803
you're stressed or need to vent,

316
00:26:06,199 --> 00:26:07,445
tell me.

317
00:26:09,276 --> 00:26:10,824
No need to smoke anymore.

318
00:26:11,524 --> 00:26:12,499
Okay?

319
00:26:15,483 --> 00:26:16,516
Okay.

320
00:26:17,724 --> 00:26:19,118
Thank you.

321
00:26:19,646 --> 00:26:21,231
P' Nalin.

322
00:26:26,536 --> 00:26:28,306
Honestly, before this...

323
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:31,059
I didn't care much about life, to be real.

324
00:26:32,940 --> 00:26:35,037
But right now,

325
00:26:37,699 --> 00:26:40,007
maybe things can get better.

326
00:26:45,679 --> 00:26:47,207
If you're using me...

327
00:26:47,634 --> 00:26:48,941
I'm willing.

328
00:26:51,011 --> 00:26:52,701
As for first place,

329
00:26:53,175 --> 00:26:54,523
I'll bring it to you.

330
00:26:55,605 --> 00:26:57,086
And I'll hold it over you later.

331
00:26:59,115 --> 00:27:00,628
Or if there's a zeroth place,

332
00:27:00,956 --> 00:27:02,903
I'll get that for you too.

333
00:27:10,019 --> 00:27:13,706
Once this is done, let's cut it and continue.

334
00:27:14,366 --> 00:27:15,574
Is this okay?

335
00:27:15,575 --> 00:27:16,626
Okay.

336
00:27:16,627 --> 00:27:18,543
Then let's split it up like this for now.

337
00:27:18,544 --> 00:27:19,116
Sure.

338
00:27:19,117 --> 00:27:20,371
P' Jane.

339
00:27:20,836 --> 00:27:22,611
Our color's water is gone.

340
00:27:23,254 --> 00:27:24,314
What?

341
00:27:24,663 --> 00:27:26,616
But we just bought several packs to refill it.

342
00:27:33,015 --> 00:27:35,470
Now I know why we run out of water so fast.

343
00:27:42,484 --> 00:27:44,379
Can you stop taking the stand's water?

344
00:27:44,380 --> 00:27:45,758
The kids don't have enough to drink.

345
00:27:51,066 --> 00:27:52,908
Can't we even share this much?

346
00:27:53,358 --> 00:27:54,718
We're on the same team.

347
00:27:55,191 --> 00:27:57,655
But you took 3,000 of our budget.

348
00:27:58,203 --> 00:28:00,456
The cheerleaders haven't bought anything to share with the stand.

349
00:28:29,789 --> 00:28:31,176
One bottle. Is that enough?

350
00:28:31,736 --> 00:28:33,234
Or do you want the whole pack?

351
00:28:33,235 --> 00:28:35,108
I'm not trying to start a fight.

352
00:28:35,550 --> 00:28:38,387
But what did you do with the 3,000 budget?

353
00:28:39,002 --> 00:28:40,555
Stop being so nosy.

354
00:28:41,095 --> 00:28:44,852
We didn't even ask how much your stupid cutouts cost.

355
00:28:44,853 --> 00:28:48,042
We have receipts for everything. Wanna see? I'll show you.

356
00:28:48,608 --> 00:28:50,221
What did you do with the money?

357
00:28:50,922 --> 00:28:52,688
Whatever we do with it is our business.

358
00:28:53,129 --> 00:28:56,324
You're only working here because we chose you.

359
00:28:58,035 --> 00:28:59,603
Don't take yourself so seriously.

360
00:29:00,529 --> 00:29:01,863
I'm working here

361
00:29:02,540 --> 00:29:04,588
because our friends chose the theme I came up with.

362
00:29:05,710 --> 00:29:07,785
You tell me, what did you do with the money?

363
00:29:08,405 --> 00:29:10,080
Paying off debts? Huh?

364
00:29:10,606 --> 00:29:11,806
Isn't that you?

365
00:29:13,150 --> 00:29:16,391
Hurry up and graduate so you can pay off your mom's debt.

366
00:29:19,752 --> 00:29:21,659
I never told anyone about my mom's debt.

367
00:29:23,063 --> 00:29:24,416
How do you know?

368
00:29:41,549 --> 00:29:42,755
It was you?

369
00:29:42,921 --> 00:29:44,743
You're the one who tore my notebook? Huh?

370
00:29:46,627 --> 00:29:47,393
Hey, hey.

371
00:29:47,394 --> 00:29:49,014
It was you who tore my notebook?

372
00:29:53,709 --> 00:29:56,623
It was you who tore my notebook. Why?

373
00:29:56,624 --> 00:29:57,936
Stop.

374
00:29:57,937 --> 00:29:59,359
Don't mess with me.

375
00:30:00,424 --> 00:30:01,991
If you're so tough, hit me.

376
00:30:01,992 --> 00:30:03,538
Let go of me, I will.

377
00:30:08,678 --> 00:30:11,178
You picked the wrong person to mess with.

378
00:30:14,254 --> 00:30:15,554
Shit.

379
00:30:20,556 --> 00:30:21,703
Are you okay?

380
00:30:21,977 --> 00:30:23,189
Are you hurt?

381
00:31:21,072 --> 00:31:22,822
Need a ride anywhere, little girl?

382
00:31:25,674 --> 00:31:28,112
My house is far, old man. Can you handle it?

383
00:31:28,113 --> 00:31:31,266
Whoa, calling me an old man? Isn't that a bit harsh?

384
00:31:32,916 --> 00:31:34,623
So why the sudden invitation?

385
00:31:34,624 --> 00:31:36,549
Usually, when I ask for a ride, you say no.

386
00:31:37,244 --> 00:31:40,252
Well, I need a favor.

387
00:31:41,420 --> 00:31:43,995
But don't worry, there's definitely compensation.

388
00:31:48,168 --> 00:31:49,381
Uh-huh.

389
00:31:49,602 --> 00:31:52,742
Hey Belle, do you believe in lucky charms?

390
00:31:53,795 --> 00:31:54,928
Yeah.

391
00:32:02,674 --> 00:32:04,100
They say

392
00:32:04,400 --> 00:32:06,542
a four-leaf clover means good luck.

393
00:32:07,115 --> 00:32:09,770
I wanted to buy one as encouragement before the competition.

394
00:32:18,885 --> 00:32:20,145
Never mind.

395
00:32:23,059 --> 00:32:25,767
I'll buy it for myself as a reward after we win.

396
00:32:26,682 --> 00:32:28,530
Let's go, before I change my mind.

397
00:32:28,531 --> 00:32:29,769
Okay.

398
00:32:32,865 --> 00:32:34,654
Here we go.

399
00:32:34,655 --> 00:32:36,676
Oh, it's hot. I just warmed it up.

400
00:32:36,677 --> 00:32:37,649
Eat a lot, Belle.

401
00:32:37,650 --> 00:32:39,068
I will, thank you.

402
00:32:40,816 --> 00:32:43,465
Does your mom usually cook at home?

403
00:32:45,485 --> 00:32:47,985
My mom has never cooked for me, not even once.

404
00:32:53,208 --> 00:32:55,630
Uh, I mean...

405
00:32:56,249 --> 00:32:57,736
I don't have a mom.

406
00:33:03,574 --> 00:33:05,360
Oh, uh...

407
00:33:05,580 --> 00:33:09,446
My mom passed away when I was little. So...

408
00:33:09,447 --> 00:33:12,361
I grew up with nannies, and mostly eat out.

409
00:33:16,388 --> 00:33:19,837
My regular customers always say my cooking

410
00:33:19,838 --> 00:33:22,449
tastes like a mother's home cooking.

411
00:33:22,449 --> 00:33:25,678
I used to give Earn some to share with her friends at school.

412
00:33:25,678 --> 00:33:27,443
I did bring it once.

413
00:33:27,444 --> 00:33:30,293
But nobody ate it. Such a waste.

414
00:33:30,294 --> 00:33:32,095
Then bring it to me next time.

415
00:33:34,545 --> 00:33:37,907
Okay, next time, I'll pack some for Earn to give you.

416
00:33:37,908 --> 00:33:39,213
Eat up.

417
00:33:39,214 --> 00:33:41,294
Okay, I'll leave you two alone.

418
00:33:41,601 --> 00:33:42,810
I'll go now.

419
00:33:42,811 --> 00:33:45,478
Since it's just you two, make sure you lock up properly.

420
00:33:47,319 --> 00:33:48,361
And turn off the lights.

421
00:33:48,362 --> 00:33:50,080
Okay.

422
00:33:56,554 --> 00:33:59,404
So, do you like the compensation?

423
00:33:59,807 --> 00:34:01,755
Um, yeah, it's good.

424
00:34:04,268 --> 00:34:06,549
But I still don't know what you need me to do.

425
00:34:07,180 --> 00:34:08,427
Well...

426
00:34:08,748 --> 00:34:11,543
I want you to help me take some pictures.

427
00:34:13,511 --> 00:34:16,094
I need to post some sexy photos.

428
00:34:16,095 --> 00:34:19,323
It's a request from a sub.

429
00:34:19,838 --> 00:34:22,935
I figured if someone else took them, they'd look better.

430
00:34:24,373 --> 00:34:27,130
But, the photos...

431
00:34:27,131 --> 00:34:28,518
Let me show you.

432
00:34:28,806 --> 00:34:31,286
It has to have ears and a tail like this.

433
00:34:34,303 --> 00:34:36,131
Is it that bad?

434
00:34:36,698 --> 00:34:39,804
Ugh, I don't want to do it anymore.

435
00:34:40,759 --> 00:34:41,992
Wait.

436
00:34:46,288 --> 00:34:47,881
No, no, I mean...

437
00:34:50,176 --> 00:34:53,082
The outfit is cute, but...

438
00:34:54,095 --> 00:34:57,058
I just imagined you in it and felt...

439
00:34:58,158 --> 00:35:02,766
Isn't it a bit too revealing?

440
00:35:04,216 --> 00:35:05,529
But...

441
00:35:05,995 --> 00:35:07,926
You've seen me in more revealing things before.

442
00:35:13,771 --> 00:35:17,097
I mean, I've shown you a bunch of them.

443
00:35:19,474 --> 00:35:20,629
Oh.

444
00:35:20,942 --> 00:35:23,528
Okay, yeah, right.

445
00:35:25,081 --> 00:35:29,316
You go ahead and eat. I'll go change.

446
00:35:29,317 --> 00:35:31,364
Come upstairs when you're done.

447
00:35:40,690 --> 00:35:41,845
Can I come in?

448
00:35:41,846 --> 00:35:43,065
Yeah.

449
00:36:02,876 --> 00:36:04,263
Why are you...

450
00:36:04,360 --> 00:36:06,123
looking at me like that?

451
00:36:08,394 --> 00:36:09,507
Like...

452
00:36:10,298 --> 00:36:11,791
what?

453
00:36:14,714 --> 00:36:16,087
Never mind.

454
00:36:31,904 --> 00:36:33,231
Do I look like a cat?

455
00:36:37,447 --> 00:36:39,411
You look cute.

456
00:36:39,412 --> 00:36:40,604
Hm?

457
00:36:40,799 --> 00:36:42,872
Uh... I mean...

458
00:36:43,239 --> 00:36:45,422
Yeah, you look like a cat.

459
00:36:48,301 --> 00:36:49,663
Um...

460
00:36:50,348 --> 00:36:51,513
So...

461
00:36:51,699 --> 00:36:52,873
Wait a sec.

462
00:37:36,051 --> 00:37:37,084
Okay.

463
00:37:38,405 --> 00:37:40,521
I'm going to take the picture now.

464
00:37:41,316 --> 00:37:42,336
Okay.

465
00:37:43,066 --> 00:37:44,202
Okay.

466
00:37:47,174 --> 00:37:49,316
1... 2...

467
00:37:50,884 --> 00:37:52,351
1... 2... 3...

468
00:37:54,133 --> 00:37:55,448
That should...

469
00:37:56,043 --> 00:37:57,509
be enough. So...

470
00:37:57,510 --> 00:37:59,838
Okay, I'll get going.

471
00:38:00,064 --> 00:38:00,801
Wait.

472
00:38:02,323 --> 00:38:04,012
Wanna get scratched by a cat?

473
00:38:04,680 --> 00:38:05,852
Sit down.

474
00:38:05,853 --> 00:38:07,760
Where are you rushing off to?

475
00:38:07,853 --> 00:38:09,703
We're not done taking pictures yet.

476
00:38:10,836 --> 00:38:12,196
Take it again.

477
00:38:13,224 --> 00:38:14,491
Okay.

478
00:39:32,861 --> 00:39:34,615
Should we keep taking pictures?

479
00:40:03,585 --> 00:40:06,582
How are you?

480
00:40:16,545 --> 00:40:21,705
You did very well today. My mom really appreciates it.

481
00:40:24,705 --> 00:40:26,425
Thank you

482
00:40:26,898 --> 00:40:32,128
Should I get my rewards then?

483
00:41:05,832 --> 00:41:06,853
Hey.

484
00:41:07,553 --> 00:41:09,593
When I reply fast, she disappears.

485
00:41:40,419 --> 00:41:43,565
Oranicha, 19 points.

486
00:41:43,981 --> 00:41:45,370
Nicharee.

487
00:41:47,368 --> 00:41:49,248
20, perfect score.

488
00:42:08,884 --> 00:42:10,399
Quit if you can.

489
00:42:11,385 --> 00:42:14,154
Don't do things that are bad for you.

490
00:42:58,860 --> 00:43:00,455
Our school...

491
00:43:00,456 --> 00:43:04,284
has a unique wai unlike anywhere else, Nicharee.

492
00:43:09,516 --> 00:43:11,867
See, you can do it if you want to.

493
00:43:19,997 --> 00:43:23,147
And there's no smell of smoke today, either.

494
00:43:25,106 --> 00:43:27,192
Do you have a cold, Sister? Is that why you can't smell it?

495
00:43:29,032 --> 00:43:32,098
Suddenly getting compliments like this is creeping me out.

496
00:44:00,225 --> 00:44:01,818
Surprise!

497
00:44:20,587 --> 00:44:22,714
[Sophie: You can stay over today. My mom's not home.]

498
00:44:26,880 --> 00:44:29,726
[Sophie: As many rounds as you want, before midnight.]

499
00:45:07,464 --> 00:45:10,106
Here are some snacks from our color's stand.

500
00:45:10,106 --> 00:45:11,796
Share them with everyone.

501
00:45:11,797 --> 00:45:14,875
Oh, thank you. Thanks.

502
00:45:16,935 --> 00:45:18,095
Jane.

503
00:45:18,873 --> 00:45:22,004
How are you doing? Did Nano slap you yesterday?

504
00:45:22,715 --> 00:45:23,915
Have you told Teacher Thip yet?

505
00:45:24,975 --> 00:45:27,505
I didn't get slapped. Just almost.

506
00:45:28,312 --> 00:45:29,418
But it's fine.

507
00:45:30,691 --> 00:45:34,443
Jane confronted her about the money, so she lost her temper.

508
00:45:34,994 --> 00:45:36,527
I'm just glad Jane's okay.

509
00:45:40,188 --> 00:45:41,344
Here's the thing.

510
00:45:41,345 --> 00:45:44,173
Nano runs a fundraising page for stray cats.

511
00:45:45,068 --> 00:45:47,899
But no one knows if she actually uses the money for the cats.

512
00:45:48,372 --> 00:45:50,885
A friend in Class D asked for proof once.

513
00:45:50,886 --> 00:45:52,045
But she couldn't get it.

514
00:45:52,371 --> 00:45:53,908
And Nano yelled at her.

515
00:45:55,746 --> 00:45:58,918
So Jane confronted her about the cheerleader budget, right?

516
00:45:59,458 --> 00:46:00,878
And it turned into this mess...

517
00:46:06,873 --> 00:46:09,516
Based on what we volunteered for last time,

518
00:46:09,517 --> 00:46:13,159
I'll have Belle and Earn compete in the French storytelling.

519
00:46:14,700 --> 00:46:16,902
Goi and Wan, you need to study more.

520
00:46:17,368 --> 00:46:19,711
Because you'll be answering general knowledge questions.

521
00:46:19,712 --> 00:46:22,886
This part of the competition is in Thai.

522
00:46:22,887 --> 00:46:25,391
I think it suits you two better.

523
00:46:25,391 --> 00:46:26,991
Because you'll probably do better than Belle.

524
00:46:32,321 --> 00:46:35,039
How many colors are on the French flag?

525
00:46:35,040 --> 00:46:36,246
Three.

526
00:46:36,247 --> 00:46:37,130
In what order?

527
00:46:37,130 --> 00:46:38,669
Red, white, blue.

528
00:46:39,912 --> 00:46:40,960
Vertical or horizontal?

529
00:46:40,960 --> 00:46:42,512
Horizontal.

530
00:46:46,813 --> 00:46:48,792
Please give this homework to Wan too.

531
00:46:48,793 --> 00:46:50,112
Finish all of this.

532
00:46:51,161 --> 00:46:51,896
Shit, wrong.

533
00:46:51,897 --> 00:46:53,121
Vertical!

534
00:46:54,810 --> 00:46:56,248
What horizontal?

535
00:46:57,092 --> 00:46:58,890
Hey, let's go home.

536
00:46:59,687 --> 00:47:01,369
I'm leaving now, P' Jane. Bye.

537
00:47:01,370 --> 00:47:03,593
Sure, get home safely. Bye.

538
00:47:27,622 --> 00:47:29,678
The poor thing is badly hurt.

539
00:47:29,678 --> 00:47:33,549
I saw your cat rescue page. Let me help with the medical bills.

540
00:47:33,980 --> 00:47:35,584
Thank you, Sister.

541
00:47:35,585 --> 00:47:37,030
I'll go now.

542
00:47:40,391 --> 00:47:43,362
Nano runs a fundraising page for stray cats.

543
00:47:43,362 --> 00:47:46,814
But no one knows if she actually uses the money for the cats.

544
00:48:25,916 --> 00:48:27,023
Why are you here?

545
00:48:28,562 --> 00:48:29,775
I'm sorry.

546
00:48:29,873 --> 00:48:31,007
Huh?

547
00:48:33,803 --> 00:48:36,520
I followed you.

548
00:48:37,717 --> 00:48:40,503
I didn't think you were actually bringing the cat to the vet.

549
00:48:45,928 --> 00:48:48,188
Just because you think I tore your notebook,

550
00:48:48,634 --> 00:48:51,020
you thought I was scamming the Sister too?

551
00:48:55,190 --> 00:48:56,963
Something like that.

552
00:48:59,036 --> 00:49:01,720
So now you know I didn't tear it?

553
00:49:02,250 --> 00:49:04,690
Wait, if you didn't do it, who did?

554
00:49:05,707 --> 00:49:08,869
You don't need to know. Just consider this an apology on their behalf.

555
00:49:09,680 --> 00:49:12,340
Because it's my fault I didn't stop them.

556
00:49:15,189 --> 00:49:17,009
I'm sorry too.

557
00:49:18,499 --> 00:49:20,374
For saying all those things to you.

558
00:49:24,193 --> 00:49:25,901
I knew it...

559
00:49:25,902 --> 00:49:29,101
Someone as pretty as you wouldn't scam anyone.

560
00:49:34,505 --> 00:49:35,983
Uh, I gotta go now.

561
00:49:36,132 --> 00:49:37,059
See ya.

562
00:49:41,425 --> 00:49:42,939
Oh, Nano.

563
00:49:43,012 --> 00:49:45,998
Don't forget to do the sports day accounting for me. Bye.

564
00:50:51,902 --> 00:50:53,356
Can we take a break?

565
00:50:54,677 --> 00:50:55,797
What's wrong?

566
00:51:01,177 --> 00:51:02,657
I just can't do it lately.

567
00:51:04,149 --> 00:51:05,902
Can we not do this?

568
00:51:07,326 --> 00:51:09,143
Let's just go back to taking pictures like before.

569
00:51:12,116 --> 00:51:13,429
We can't, Earn.

570
00:51:13,780 --> 00:51:16,020
It's not like when we first started.

571
00:51:16,568 --> 00:51:19,785
Pictures alone just don't sell anymore. It has to be videos.

572
00:51:29,593 --> 00:51:30,706
Earn.

573
00:51:35,706 --> 00:51:40,037
Like... it just has to be videos now.

574
00:51:41,774 --> 00:51:44,824
The girl-on-girl market isn't even that big.

575
00:51:45,781 --> 00:51:48,120
Especially with our faces hidden like this.

576
00:51:48,707 --> 00:51:51,733
But if we show our faces,

577
00:51:51,734 --> 00:51:54,890
we could get 100,000 right from the first time, Earn.

578
00:51:54,891 --> 00:51:56,034
P' Som.

579
00:51:56,474 --> 00:51:58,697
I told you I'm not going to show my face.

580
00:52:00,488 --> 00:52:02,721
Please, I really can't do this.

581
00:53:11,704 --> 00:53:12,837
Aioon.

582
00:53:13,024 --> 00:53:14,518
Wanna try shooting?

583
00:53:14,519 --> 00:53:16,070
But I don't know how to play.

584
00:53:16,071 --> 00:53:18,640
It's okay. I'll have my friends teach you.

585
00:53:20,291 --> 00:53:22,143
Hey, teach her how to shoot.

586
00:53:23,489 --> 00:53:24,196
Here.

587
00:53:24,447 --> 00:53:25,307
Have you ever played?

588
00:53:25,308 --> 00:53:26,442
Never.

589
00:53:27,609 --> 00:53:29,044
Do it like this.

590
00:53:29,045 --> 00:53:30,784
Here, hold it.

591
00:53:34,494 --> 00:53:35,380
Like this.

592
00:53:35,380 --> 00:53:36,747
Like this?

593
00:53:36,747 --> 00:53:39,420
And then aim, and throw it into the hoop.

594
00:53:44,164 --> 00:53:46,172
Almost made it. Try again.

595
00:53:49,738 --> 00:53:52,385
One, two, three.

596
00:54:39,160 --> 00:54:40,553
Hey!

597
00:54:44,944 --> 00:54:46,050
Are you okay?

598
00:54:48,736 --> 00:54:49,930
Let's go.

599
00:55:06,048 --> 00:55:07,855
Does it hurt anywhere, Sophie?

600
00:55:16,039 --> 00:55:18,580
If something is bothering you, you can tell me.

601
00:55:20,771 --> 00:55:22,565
I was just walking too fast.

602
00:55:22,566 --> 00:55:24,291
So I wasn't careful.

603
00:55:29,140 --> 00:55:31,926
I was watching the basketball practice earlier.

604
00:55:31,927 --> 00:55:36,227
I totally understand why everyone adores Amy.

605
00:55:38,953 --> 00:55:40,730
Things are great these days.

606
00:55:41,851 --> 00:55:46,904
If you want to scream for someone, you can, and no one will judge you.

607
00:55:46,905 --> 00:55:49,761
But back in my day, oh my.

608
00:55:49,761 --> 00:55:52,833
Screaming like that would get you punished.

609
00:55:54,488 --> 00:55:56,638
Not to mention dating.

610
00:56:00,240 --> 00:56:01,397
And...

611
00:56:01,821 --> 00:56:06,258
In your day, were there many students who liked each other in school?

612
00:56:08,512 --> 00:56:12,342
In any era, there are always students who like each other in school.

613
00:56:15,100 --> 00:56:16,623
Parents...

614
00:56:16,624 --> 00:56:19,452
often think that sending their kids to an all-girls school

615
00:56:20,305 --> 00:56:22,807
will keep them away from romance.

616
00:56:23,564 --> 00:56:25,130
Because there are no boys.

617
00:56:26,174 --> 00:56:28,051
But the truth is,

618
00:56:28,051 --> 00:56:30,755
love doesn't discriminate.

619
00:56:36,702 --> 00:56:38,202
My first love...

620
00:56:39,305 --> 00:56:41,232
happened right here in this school.

621
00:56:46,676 --> 00:56:49,210
Back then, I could only wonder...

622
00:56:49,884 --> 00:56:52,111
If love is a good thing,

623
00:56:55,148 --> 00:56:57,632
then why is our love considered wrong?

624
00:57:02,142 --> 00:57:03,937
I still think that way now.

625
00:57:16,738 --> 00:57:18,476
Yes, P' Title, what's up?

626
00:57:19,176 --> 00:57:22,520
Nano, I've transferred the money for last month's event.

627
00:57:23,164 --> 00:57:25,104
Thank you so much.

628
00:57:25,379 --> 00:57:28,125
If there's more work, I'll take you to the casting. Okay?

629
00:57:28,644 --> 00:57:30,077
Sure.

630
00:57:30,078 --> 00:57:32,883
Call me anytime. I really want to work.

631
00:57:33,538 --> 00:57:35,425
Okay, thank you.

632
00:57:40,514 --> 00:57:42,890
Wow, really?

633
00:57:42,891 --> 00:57:45,533
Has Nano sunk so low as to borrow from Khaopan?

634
00:57:45,833 --> 00:57:48,503
Yeah, Khaopan told me the other day.

635
00:57:49,654 --> 00:57:51,194
That's just sad.

636
00:57:51,195 --> 00:57:53,111
Borrowing from someone poorer than her?

637
00:57:54,159 --> 00:57:55,572
If she's actually poorer.

638
00:57:56,011 --> 00:57:58,832
I heard Class B talking the other day too.

639
00:57:58,840 --> 00:58:01,047
Nano borrowed from them as well.

640
00:58:01,770 --> 00:58:03,172
What's going on?

641
00:58:03,674 --> 00:58:05,705
Is she going to borrow from the whole world?

642
00:58:23,560 --> 00:58:25,670
Did you come see me at the basketball court earlier?

643
00:58:29,546 --> 00:58:30,698
Yeah.

644
00:58:31,269 --> 00:58:34,469
So why didn't you come say hi?

645
00:58:34,762 --> 00:58:36,695
You just disappeared.

646
00:58:38,872 --> 00:58:40,414
I saw you were busy.

647
00:58:44,341 --> 00:58:45,495
Jealous?

648
00:58:47,619 --> 00:58:49,012
Why would I be?

649
00:58:49,654 --> 00:58:51,889
I'm just one of the people you're talking to.

650
00:58:52,844 --> 00:58:55,454
Look at you, all jealous

651
00:58:55,809 --> 00:58:57,481
and feeling neglected.

652
00:59:01,604 --> 00:59:03,097
I was just annoyed

653
00:59:03,694 --> 00:59:05,302
that I texted and no one replied.

654
00:59:07,693 --> 00:59:10,075
My phone was in the locker.

655
00:59:10,252 --> 00:59:11,932
Because I was practicing.

656
00:59:13,665 --> 00:59:14,858
Right.

657
00:59:15,106 --> 00:59:16,579
Whatever you say.

658
00:59:24,812 --> 00:59:26,105
Hey.

659
00:59:26,106 --> 00:59:28,571
You're not just one of the people I'm talking to.

660
00:59:29,644 --> 00:59:31,444
Since I started talking to you,

661
00:59:32,270 --> 00:59:34,385
I haven't been with anyone else.

662
00:59:37,442 --> 00:59:40,158
You're the one who leaves me on read.

663
00:59:40,159 --> 00:59:42,827
I waited so long last night I couldn't sleep.

664
00:59:43,307 --> 00:59:45,435
I never leave you on read.

665
00:59:50,411 --> 00:59:52,031
I'm sorry.

666
00:59:52,875 --> 00:59:55,705
My mom came in to check if I was asleep.

667
00:59:56,500 --> 00:59:58,120
So I had to turn off my phone.

668
01:00:00,693 --> 01:00:03,590
Oh, and about coming to the court...

669
01:00:03,591 --> 01:00:04,890
Did you need something?

670
01:00:06,498 --> 01:00:07,858
Well...

671
01:00:08,297 --> 01:00:10,577
My mom invited you to come hang out with us this Saturday.

672
01:00:10,937 --> 01:00:13,614
But I told her you have basketball practice.

673
01:00:14,293 --> 01:00:16,610
Nah, I'm not practicing.

674
01:00:17,219 --> 01:00:18,499
Why would I?

675
01:00:21,531 --> 01:00:23,430
It's your birthday this Saturday.

676
01:00:23,431 --> 01:00:26,860
Like I'd forget Sophie's birthday.

677
01:00:32,683 --> 01:00:34,777
Isn't basketball practice important?

678
01:00:35,460 --> 01:00:38,451
If you lose, your fans will be disappointed.

679
01:00:40,035 --> 01:00:42,570
Nothing is more important than how you feel.

680
01:00:50,895 --> 01:00:52,024
Forgot.

681
01:00:52,677 --> 01:00:53,839
There's a camera.

682
01:00:57,109 --> 01:00:58,887
It's been broken for ages.

683
01:01:00,218 --> 01:01:01,798
I haven't reported it yet.

684
01:01:02,821 --> 01:01:04,269
So it hasn't been fixed.

685
01:01:40,972 --> 01:01:43,990
Hey, can we just get the 4,500 zone today?

686
01:01:45,020 --> 01:01:48,313
Let's just go for VIP. It's just a little more for a signed poster.

687
01:01:49,123 --> 01:01:51,149
Here, Earn, here.

688
01:01:53,322 --> 01:01:55,126
Can you pay me back today?

689
01:01:55,849 --> 01:01:56,874
How much?

690
01:01:57,096 --> 01:01:58,236
Ten thousand.

691
01:01:59,741 --> 01:02:02,513
Hey, hey, it's starting.

692
01:02:02,514 --> 01:02:03,690
Okay.

693
01:02:04,085 --> 01:02:05,214
53

694
01:02:05,214 --> 01:02:06,241
54

695
01:02:06,242 --> 01:02:07,155
55

696
01:02:07,163 --> 01:02:08,114
56

697
01:02:08,115 --> 01:02:09,094
57

698
01:02:09,095 --> 01:02:09,776
58

699
01:02:09,777 --> 01:02:10,755
Refresh now.

700
01:02:10,756 --> 01:02:13,222
Damn it! Mine is still loading.

701
01:02:13,223 --> 01:02:15,136
This is bad. Shit!

702
01:02:15,136 --> 01:02:16,250
It's not loading at all.

703
01:02:16,250 --> 01:02:17,116
What do we do?

704
01:02:17,116 --> 01:02:18,001
I want this zone.

705
01:02:18,001 --> 01:02:19,650
If you're free, book it.

706
01:02:21,786 --> 01:02:24,368
Yay! I got 3 VIP tickets.

707
01:02:24,368 --> 01:02:26,531
Awesome. Transfer the money to our friend at 7-Eleven to pay.

708
01:02:26,531 --> 01:02:27,537
Okay.

709
01:02:31,925 --> 01:02:34,515
Earn, can Pan borrow from you first?

710
01:02:36,583 --> 01:02:38,798
Earn, you don't need to.

711
01:02:41,115 --> 01:02:42,730
I'm seriously asking you.

712
01:02:42,731 --> 01:02:44,857
Do you have money problems lately?

713
01:02:45,527 --> 01:02:47,426
You've put me off so many times.

714
01:02:52,300 --> 01:02:56,483
Well, if you became color president, you would've gotten your money back long ago.

715
01:02:56,484 --> 01:02:58,601
But you lost to that Jane.

716
01:02:58,602 --> 01:03:01,509
And you gossiped about me to other classes, right?

717
01:03:08,226 --> 01:03:09,986
Don't try to change the subject.

718
01:03:11,428 --> 01:03:12,974
What you need to do right now,

719
01:03:14,067 --> 01:03:15,740
is transfer my money back.

720
01:03:21,934 --> 01:03:23,074
Transferred.

721
01:03:23,669 --> 01:03:25,610
Go spend it on your boys.

722
01:03:26,123 --> 01:03:27,310
Thanks.

723
01:03:38,782 --> 01:03:39,982
Did you tell her?

724
01:03:40,445 --> 01:03:42,525
That I was talking about her to other people?

725
01:03:43,890 --> 01:03:45,138
I didn't.

726
01:03:45,485 --> 01:03:47,603
If it wasn't you, then who was it, Earn?

727
01:03:47,604 --> 01:03:49,689
You're the only one I told.

728
01:03:50,590 --> 01:03:52,105
Hey, guys.

729
01:03:53,572 --> 01:03:56,535
If you're done getting tickets, I'd like to get back to studying.

730
01:03:57,388 --> 01:03:59,149
Because we can only use this room until 6.

731
01:04:10,774 --> 01:04:11,815
Belle.

732
01:04:13,474 --> 01:04:15,442
I'm really asking you.

733
01:04:16,622 --> 01:04:19,359
Since when did you start paying attention in class?

734
01:04:20,987 --> 01:04:22,174
Or is it...

735
01:04:22,762 --> 01:04:25,820
since Teacher Nalin started teaching?

736
01:04:27,283 --> 01:04:30,765
Belle, she's totally your type, right?

737
01:04:31,541 --> 01:04:32,875
Just like Teacher Som.

738
01:04:36,716 --> 01:04:37,916
Get out.

739
01:04:38,253 --> 01:04:39,433
I'm not leaving.

740
01:04:40,263 --> 01:04:41,710
Why, Belle?

741
01:04:41,947 --> 01:04:44,394
Or are you going to run home and cry to your mom?

742
01:04:45,595 --> 01:04:47,062
Say that again.

743
01:04:47,630 --> 01:04:52,306
I said, run home and cry to your mom!

744
01:04:52,307 --> 01:04:53,121
Hey!

745
01:04:53,121 --> 01:04:54,867
What's wrong with you?

746
01:04:54,867 --> 01:04:55,792
Don't...

747
01:04:55,792 --> 01:04:56,970
Shit!

748
01:04:59,422 --> 01:05:01,496
What the hell are you saying?

749
01:05:01,497 --> 01:05:03,002
So what, motherless freak!

750
01:05:05,501 --> 01:05:06,790
Stop!

751
01:05:08,982 --> 01:05:10,429
Everyone, stop!

